   Programme; Int Dendrol Soc; Royal Botan Gardens; Royal Horticultural Soc},
Abstract = {Separation of Taxus and allied genera of Taxaceae as the order Taxales
   seems unjustified. The authors summarise a theory explaining the
   evolution of the ovulate structure including a primary and secondary
   shoot, and believe that this helps to explain many of the unusual
   morphological features found in Taxus. Other features such as
   pollination drop, pollination mechanism and non-saccate pollen are
   similar to their analogues in Cupressaceae and the authors consider
   Taxus to be a member of Coniferales.},
